ng those years. Similarly, volcanic eruptions can cause short-term cooling effects that can last for several years, making it essential to include short-term weather patterns in climate predictions.\\n\\nMoreover, recent advances in climate modeling have shown that incorporating short-term weather patterns into climate predictions can improve their accuracy and relevance. For instance, some climate models now use ensemble forecasting, which combines multiple simulations to generate a range of possible future states of the climate system, including the effects of short-term weather patterns.\\n\\nIn conclusion, while there is merit to the argument that weather and climate are distinct entities,\"\n"label: true
